SIMPLE: disfigurement
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Disfigurement
<hw>Dis*fig"ure*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Act of disfiguring, or state of being disfigured; deformity.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which disfigures; a defacement; a
blot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Uncommon expressions . . . are a <qex>disfigurement</qex> rather
than any embellishment of discourse.</q> <rj><qau>Hume.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disfigurer</ent>⟦br⟧
